## Section 2 â€” IRSA Policy

### Credential Prohibition

Hardcoded AWS credentials are **prohibited** in all contexts:
- Terraform configurations
- Kubernetes manifests and environment variables
- Application source code
- CI/CD pipeline definitions

Prohibited credential keys (must never appear as values): `AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID`,
`AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY`, `AWS_SESSION_TOKEN`, `aws_access_key_id`,
`aws_secret_access_key`, `aws_session_token`.

If any of these appear as hardcoded values in existing manifests or code, flag
them and instruct the developer to remove them immediately.

### LRAH Module Auto-Grant

The LRAH Terraform module automatically grants the SA role access to every AWS
resource added to the corresponding map entry (`s3_buckets`, `sqs_queues`, etc.).
No additional IAM configuration is required from the developer. Do not instruct
the developer to create or modify IAM policies manually.

For SQS specifically: LRAH creates both `SQS-{account-id}-{env-id}-Read` and
`SQS-{account-id}-{env-id}-ReadWrite` policies for the environment and attaches
them to the existing SA role from ConfigMap `sa-role-{account-id}-{env-id}`.
No new IAM role is created for SQS access.

